Responsibilities
You will be responsible to provide operational and administrative support to the Clinical Operations Department. This involves working closely with key stakeholders to develop, implement and monitor clinical-related projects; KPI tracking and reporting; performing secretariat duties, oversee operational workflows and assist in process improvment activities.

Requirements

  Bachelor’s Degree
  2 or more years of working experience (healthcare experience with practical aspects of hospital operations preferred)
  Meticulous, analytical with good organisational and coordination skills.
  Good interpersonal and communication (written and verbal) skills.
  Able to work well independently and as a team member.
  Able to exercise initiative, manage pressure, multi-task and work independently in a fast-paced environment is a must.
  Proficiency in MS office applications and a flair for numbers is essential.
  Added advantage if familiar with concepts of project management, budget and office administration.
